HEADWORD: Teutonicism
<hw>Teu*ton"i*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mode of
speech peculiar to the Teutons; a Teutonic idiom, phrase, or expression;
a Teutonic mode or custom; a Germanism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

